        (
        R
        →
        Q
        )
        
          
            )
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\big (}R\to (P\to Q){\big )}\equiv {\big (}(R\to P)\to (R\to Q){\big )}}
  Similarly, on classical interpretations of the other connectives, material implication validates the following entailments:

Antecedent strengthening: 
  
    
      
        P
        →
        Q
        ⊨
        (
        P
        ∧
        R
        )
        →
        Q
      
    
    {\displaystyle P\to Q\models (P\land R)\to Q}
  
Vacuous conditional: 
  
    
      
        ¬
        P
        ⊨
        P
        →
        Q
      
    
    {\displaystyle \neg P\models P\to Q}
  
